    "created_at": "2016-09-26T23:20:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-26T23:20:03Z",
    "body": "@bholley if `T` is not a sized type (like `str`), then `*mut str` is actually 2 pointers large instead of 1 (unlike `*const String`, which is one pointer large).\n\nIn that sense the implementation of `AtomicPtr` is radically different for `T: ?Sized`, which is what's not implemented yet (doubleword atomics)\n",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
